construct on said Land, in a good and workmanlike manner in accordance herewith and with the
plans and specifications ("Plans") therefor agreed upon by Owner and Contractor and approved
by Bank and all building codes and other requirements of any governmental, utility district or
municipal authority having jurisdiction, the following improvements:
The construction of a new single-family home for primary residence (homestead).
Contractor Work. Contractor agrees to immediately commence the performance
of this Contract and to work diligently and without unreasonable cessation of work in the
construction of the improvements provided for in said Plans and to complete the improvements
on or before January, 26, 2022; subject only to delays due to causes beyond Contractor's control
such as acts of God, inclement weather, availability of materials and other causes normally
included within the term "force majeure".
Contract Suin and Payment. For and in consideration of the foregoing undertaking
on the part of Contractor, Owner shall pay or cause to be paid to Contractor the sum of THREE
HUNDRED THIRTY THREE THOUSAND SEVEN HUNDRED FORTY FOUR AND
NO/100s DOLLARS ($333,744.00) ("Contract Sum"). Of said Contract Sum, TWO
HUNDRED NINETY SEVEN THOUSAND FIVE HUNDRED AND NO/100s DOLLARS
($297,500.00) is to be advanced| to Contractor by Bank in accordance with the terms and
provisions of an agreement ("Tri-Party Agreement") of even date herewith by and among Owner,
Contractor and Bank, The Loan Amount is to be advanced by Bank for and on behalf of Owner
and at their express instance and request and will be evidenced by a promissory note ("Note") of
even date herewith from the Owner to Bank in the principal sum of TWO HUNDRED NINETY
SEVEN THOUSAND FIVE HUNDRED AND NO/100s DOLLARS ($297,500.00), said Note
bearing interest as therein provided from its date until maturity, the principal of said Note and all
interest accruing thereon being payable as therein provided, and payment of said Note being
secured by the liens granted in this Contract and, in addition thereto, the lien and security interest
of a Deed of Trust ("Deed of Trust") of even date herewith from Owner in favor of Bank. The
Note, to the extent of TWO HUNDRED NINETY SEVEN THOUSAND FIVE HUNDRED
AND NO/100s DOLLARS ($297,500.00), of the cash advanced or to be advanced as evidenced
by the Note shall be utilized only for construction of improvements on the property described
herein.
5.
Lien to Secure Note. To secure payment of the advances to Contractor by Bank at
the request of Owner, as evidenced by the Note, and the interest and other sums payable
thereunder, Owner hereby gives and grants to-Contractor a mechanic's, materialman's,
contractor's, and laborer's lien as provided by the Constitution and laws of the State of Texas, on
the land and all improvements now or hereafter constructed thereon and all easements, rights and
appurtenances thereunto belonging, all of which shall be deemed to be and remain a part of the
property covered by this Contract; and Owner agrees that said liens, may be sold and transferred
to Bank and that Bank, its successors and assigns shall have, and, be| subrogated to, all of the lien
rights and equities of Contractor;
